[*] LibDataBroker-1.1
[*] LibDBIcon-1.0
[/list]

[hr]

[size=5][color=#f8b700]FAQ[/color][/size]

[b]Q: Where does the BIS data come from?[/b]
A: All BIS lists are sourced from [url=https://www.icy-veins.com/wow/class-guides]Icy Veins[/url] class guides for Midnight Season 1. Data is embedded in the addon and updated with each release.

[b]Q: Can the addon fetch BIS data live from Icy Veins?[/b]
A: No. WoW addons run in a sandboxed Lua environment with no HTTP access. The data is updated manually with each addon version.

[b]Q: Why don't I see any upgrades for a player?[/b]
A: Either the player already has all their BIS items equipped, their spec isn't recognized, or they were out of inspect range during the scan. Try rescanning.

[b]Q: Does it work in raids?[/b]
A: Yes! It scans all raid members too. The scoring still focuses on M+ dungeon drops, but you can switch to Raid mode to see which raid items each player needs.

[b]Q: What about crafted items and Catalyst pieces?[/b]
A: Crafted items and Matrix Catalyst pieces appear in the BIS lists but don't count toward dungeon scoring since they aren't dungeon drops.

